<DOC><DOCNO> AP880702-0141 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-02-88 1708EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Syria-Missiles     07-02 0195</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Syria-Missiles,0199</SECOND><HEAD>Syria Denies Reports It Plans to Buy Chinese Missiles</HEAD><DATELINE>DAMASCUS, Syria (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A military spokesman on Saturday deniedreports Syria was planning to buy advanced surface-to-surfacemissiles from China.   News reports last month quoted Israeli officials as saying thegovernment of President Hafez Assad was discussing with China thepossibilty of purchasing the missile that is still in theexperimental stage.   ``The real fact which is very well known to the Israelis is thatthere is no such deal between Syria and China and there is nodiscussion about it,'' said the Syrian military spokesman speakingon condition of anonymity.   He said Syria has the missiles needed for its defense andaccused Israel of spreading the rumor as a ploy to get moreAmerican aid.   The news reports said Syria was intending to buy the M-9missile, which has an estimated range of 375 miles. China may havetested the missile for the first time in June, according to thereports.   Israeli officials said the missile could be a serious threat toIsrael and could be armed with chemical weapons. But they said theyhad no information of an imminent sale.</TEXT></DOC>